{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"Paying close attention to something:"},{"time":3280,"text":"Not that easy, is it?"},{"time":5520,"text":"It's because our attention is pulled\nin so many different directions at a time,"},{"time":10560,"text":"and it's in fact pretty impressive\nif you can stay focused."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16360,"text":"Many people think that attention\nis all about what we are focusing on,"},{"time":20440,"text":"but it's also about what information\nour brain is trying to filter out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26320,"text":"There are two ways\nyou direct your attention."},{"time":29600,"text":"First, there's overt attention."},{"time":31640,"text":"In overt attention,\nyou move your eyes towards something"},{"time":35800,"text":"in order to pay attention to it."},{"time":38360,"text":"Then there's covert attention."},{"time":40360,"text":"In covert attention,\nyou pay attention to something,"},{"time":44400,"text":"but without moving your eyes."},{"time":47040,"text":"Think of driving for a second."},{"time":50960,"text":"Your overt attention,\nyour direction of the eyes,"},{"time":54000,"text":"are in front,"},{"time":55680,"text":"but that's your covert attention"},{"time":57480,"text":"which is constantly scanning\nthe surrounding area,"},{"time":61600,"text":"where you don't actually look at them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65519,"text":"I'm a computational neuroscientist,"},{"time":67480,"text":"and I work on cognitive\nbrain-machine interfaces,"},{"time":70600,"text":"or bringing together\nthe brain and the computer."},{"time":74720,"text":"I love brain patterns."},{"time":76720,"text":"Brain patterns are important for us"},{"time":78440,"text":"because based on them\nwe can build models for the computers,"},{"time":81960,"text":"and based on these models"},{"time":83400,"text":"computers can recognize\nhow well our brain functions."},{"time":87640,"text":"And if it doesn't function well,"},{"time":90080,"text":"then these computers themselves\ncan be used as assistive devices"},{"time":94760,"text":"for therapies."},{"time":96480,"text":"But that also means something,"},{"time":99360,"text":"because choosing the wrong patterns"},{"time":101880,"text":"will give us the wrong models"},{"time":103800,"text":"and therefore the wrong therapies."},{"time":105480,"text":"Right?"},{"time":107640,"text":"In case of attention,"},{"time":109320,"text":"the fact that we can"},{"time":111800,"text":"shift our attention not only by our eyes"},{"time":115320,"text":"but also by thinking --"},{"time":117440,"text":"that makes covert attention\nan interesting model for computers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122280,"text":"So I wanted to know\nwhat are the brainwave patterns"},{"time":125760,"text":"when you look overtly\nor when you look covertly."},{"time":130440,"text":"I set up an experiment for that."},{"time":132960,"text":"In this experiment\nthere are two flickering squares,"},{"time":135720,"text":"one of them flickering\nat a slower rate than the other one."},{"time":140600,"text":"Depending on which of these flickers\nyou are paying attention to,"},{"time":144440,"text":"certain parts of your brain\nwill start resonating in the same rate"},{"time":149200,"text":"as that flickering rate."},{"time":152000,"text":"So by analyzing your brain signals,"},{"time":154960,"text":"we can track where exactly\nyou are watching"},{"time":158760,"text":"or you are paying attention to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"So to see what happens in your brain\nwhen you pay overt attention,"},{"time":167240,"text":"I asked people to look directly\nin one of the squares"},{"time":170520,"text":"and pay attention to it."},{"time":172760,"text":"In this case, not surprisingly,\nwe saw that these flickering squares"},{"time":178080,"text":"appeared in their brain signals"},{"time":180040,"text":"which was coming\nfrom the back of their head,"},{"time":183560,"text":"which is responsible for the processing\nof your visual information."},{"time":188280,"text":"But I was really interested"},{"time":190640,"text":"to see what happens in your brain\nwhen you pay covert attention."},{"time":194480,"text":"So this time I asked people\nto look in the middle of the screen"},{"time":198400,"text":"and without moving their eyes,"},{"time":201120,"text":"to pay attention\nto either of these squares."},{"time":205120,"text":"When we did that,"},{"time":206760,"text":"we saw that both of these flickering rates\nappeared in their brain signals,"},{"time":210720,"text":"but interestingly,"},{"time":212640,"text":"only one of them,\nwhich was paid attention to,"},{"time":216200,"text":"had stronger signals,"},{"time":217880,"text":"so there was something in the brain"},{"time":220160,"text":"which was handling this information"},{"time":222720,"text":"so that thing in the brain was basically\nthe activation of the frontal area."},{"time":230440,"text":"The front part of your brain\nis responsible"},{"time":233440,"text":"for higher cognitive functions as a human."},{"time":237160,"text":"The frontal part,\nit seems that it works as a filter"},{"time":242640,"text":"trying to let information come in\nonly from the right flicker"},{"time":247040,"text":"that you are paying attention to"},{"time":249400,"text":"and trying to inhibit the information\ncoming from the ignored one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255400,"text":"The filtering ability of the brain\nis indeed a key for attention,"},{"time":260720,"text":"which is missing in some people,"},{"time":263520,"text":"for example in people with ADHD."},{"time":266640,"text":"So a person with ADHD\ncannot inhibit these distractors,"},{"time":271680,"text":"and that's why they can't focus\nfor a long time on a single task."},{"time":277600,"text":"But what if this person"},{"time":279160,"text":"could play a specific computer game"},{"time":282720,"text":"with his brain connected to the computer,"},{"time":286440,"text":"and then train his own brain"},{"time":289360,"text":"to inhibit these distractors?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293680,"text":"Well, ADHD is just one example."},{"time":297200,"text":"We can use these cognitive\nbrain-machine interfaces"},{"time":300480,"text":"for many other cognitive fields."},{"time":303760,"text":"It was just a few years ago"},{"time":305560,"text":"that my grandfather had a stroke,\nand he lost complete ability to speak."},{"time":312640,"text":"He could understand everybody,\nbut there was no way to respond,"},{"time":316000,"text":"even not writing\nbecause he was illiterate."},{"time":320000,"text":"So he passed away in silence."},{"time":324800,"text":"I remember thinking at that time:"},{"time":327160,"text":"What if we could have a computer"},{"time":331080,"text":"which could speak for him?"},{"time":333840,"text":"Now, after years that I am in this field,"},{"time":336080,"text":"I can see that this might be possible."},{"time":340240,"text":"Imagine if we can find brainwave patterns"},{"time":343120,"text":"when people think\nabout images or even letters,"},{"time":347720,"text":"like the letter A generates\na different brainwave pattern"},{"time":350680,"text":"than the letter B, and so on."},{"time":352960,"text":"Could a computer one day\ncommunicate for people who can't speak?"},{"time":357640,"text":"What if a computer"},{"time":359960,"text":"can help us understand\nthe thoughts of a person in a coma?"},{"time":365840,"text":"We are not there yet,"},{"time":367480,"text":"but pay close attention."},{"time":370240,"text":"We will be there soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371960,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373480,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}